HEADWORD: Stand-by
<hw>Stand"-by`</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧nd"b⟦imac⟧`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>One who, or that which, stands by one in need; something upon which
one relies for constant use or in an emergency.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

